                <h4>About the Author</h4>
                <p>He is a founding member of <a href="http://www.a-i-t.net/en/" class="out">Arts Initiative Tokyo</a> (<span class="sc">AIT</span>) and currently serves as deputy director. He was a curator at the 21st Century Museum of Contemporary Art in Kanazawa and the NTT InterCommunication Center in Tokyo, and senior curator at the Museum of Contemporary Art, Tokyo.</p>
                <p>Among his independent projects, he was co-curator of <em>Rapt! – 20 Contemporary Artists from Japan</em> (Various venues, Australia, 2006), <em>Beautiful New World: Contemporary Visual Culture from Japan</em> (“798” Dashanzi Art District and Guangdong Museum of Art, 2007), and the 3rd Nanjing Triennial, 2008. He was the artistic director of the Festival for Arts and Social Technology Yokohama [CREAM] 2009, and a co-curator of Media_City Seoul 2010. He is currently a curator for Beppu Art Project 2012 and <a href="http://aichitriennale.jp/english/index.html" class="out">Aichi Triennale 2013</a>, as well as adjunct curator of the Maebashi Art Museum which will open in 2013. He is the co-editor of <a href="http://www.amazon.co.uk/From-Postwar-Postmodern-Japan-1945-1989/dp/0822353687" class="out"><em>From the Postwar to the Postmodern, Art in Japan 1945–1989: Primary Documents</em></a> (Museum of Modern Art New York, 2012).</p>
